# Allow-list approach: ignore everything by default, then re-include only
# what `docker/Dockerfile` actually needs from the build context.
#
# This keeps the build context small and prevents accidental inclusion of
# source trees, IDE state, secrets, or other workspace files in the image.

**

# Pre-built Felix runtime (laid down by the build pipeline before `docker build`).
!felix-dist/

# Container packaging files referenced by the Dockerfile.
!docker/Dockerfile
!docker/entrypoint.sh
!docker/THIRD_PARTY_LICENSES.md
!docker/initial-repository/
!docker/initial-repository/**

# Defensive overrides: never include these even if a future allow-list entry
# would otherwise pull them in.
**/.git
**/.gitignore
**/.DS_Store
**/Thumbs.db
**/.vscode/
**/.idea/
**/*.log
**/node_modules/
